{
  "text": "The modified GOLD criteria [CITATION_1] are a very useful tool for diagnosing and assessing the severity of COPD through simple spirometry without lung volume measurements in clinical settings [CITATION_2] . However, there are no specific guidelines for diagnosing mixed pattern. The 2005 ATS/ERS guidelines [CITATION_3] cannot be used with spirometry data alone due to lack of information on lung volumes.",
